B17 - Implement one state-of-the-art solution and evaluate it

Objective
The goal of thi activity was to implement a modern cybersecurity solution and evaluate its effectiveness in improving account security.

Method
I implemented Multi-Factor Authentication on my school account using the Microsoft Authenticator app. This involved setting up an additional verification step required during login.

Implementation
MFA was enabled by linking my school accountr to the Microsoft Authenticator app. After setup, logging into the account required both my password and a verification approval or code generated by this app.

Evaluation
Strengths:
- provides strong protection against unauthorised access
- prevents attackers from accessing the account even if the password is compromised
- easy to use after initial setup
Limitations:
- requires access to a mobile device
- slight delay during login due to verification step

Outcome
The implementation successfully added an extra layer of security to my school account, significantly reducing the risk of account compromise.

Reflection
This activity demonstrated how practical and effective modern security solutions like MFA are in real-world use. It reinforced the impoertance of implementing additional security layers rather than relying solely on passwords.
